    Scope and Contents
Rice discusses his coal mining experiences in Coulterville, Illinois: tools, mining exams, drivers, cleaning tracks, safety and hazards, mining buckets, union conflicts, and the Mulkeytown March.  He also discusses growing up in a coal mining family, early schooling, chores, and living in company houses. 2 tapes, 120 mins.
Interview by Barbara Herndon, 1977 
